      <article class="speculative-card">
        <div class="speculative-number">01</div>
        <h3 class="speculative-title">The Thinking Room</h3>
        <div class="speculative-body">
          <p>Imagine you are planning your business. You sit in a quiet room. Details keep coming and you voice them without interruption.</p>
          <p>Your agent listens. It doesn&rsquo;t interrupt. But you can ask it anytime: <em>&ldquo;What am I missing? Where are my blind spots? What cognitive biases am I falling into?&rdquo;</em></p>
          <p>When you&rsquo;re done, it gives you back your thinking &mdash; as a presentation, a voice message, a short text, a video. You decide the format.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speculative-output">
          <span class="output-label">Output:</span>
          <span class="output-options">presentation ¬∑ voice memo ¬∑ text ¬∑ video</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Story 2: The Second Opinion -->
      <article class="speculative-card">
        <div class="speculative-number">02</div>
        <h3 class="speculative-title">The Second Opinion</h3>
        <div class="speculative-body">
          <p>Before you share your idea publicly, you stress-test it. The agent plays devil&rsquo;s advocate. It finds the weak points you can&rsquo;t see because you&rsquo;re too close.</p>
          <p>But it also stress-checks your mind. <em>&ldquo;Is this actually a crisis, or am I catastrophizing?&rdquo;</em></p>
          <p>It separates signal from noise when anxiety amplifies everything. Not therapy. Just a reality check from something that doesn&rsquo;t have skin in the game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speculative-output">
          <span class="output-label">Mode:</span>
